sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant UI as Orion UI
    participant Wizard as BYO Wizard
    participant Backend as Orion Backend
    participant KC as Keycloak
    participant RHAO as Red Hat Agent Operator
    participant K8s as Kubernetes
    participant Pod as Agent Pod

    rect rgb(238, 242, 255)
    Note over User,Wizard: BYO Agent Wizard
    User->>UI: Click "+ New Agent"
    UI->>UI: Open Intent Dialog
    User->>UI: Select "BYO Agent"
    UI->>Wizard: Open CreateAgentWizard
    end

    rect rgb(219, 234, 254)
    Note over Wizard,Backend: Step 1 - Basics
    Wizard->>Backend: GET /kagenti/namespaces
    Wizard->>Backend: GET /kagenti/agents/build-strategies
    Backend->>RHAO: GET /api/v1/namespaces
    RHAO-->>Backend: [enabled namespaces]
    Backend-->>Wizard: Populate namespace dropdown
    User->>Wizard: Enter name, namespace, framework
    end

    rect rgb(219, 234, 254)
    Note over Wizard: Step 2 - Deployment
    User->>Wizard: Select "Container Image"
    User->>Wizard: Enter image URL + pull secret
    end

    rect rgb(219, 234, 254)
    Note over Wizard: Step 3 - Runtime
    User->>Wizard: Add env vars, ports
    User->>Wizard: Toggle HTTP route, auth bridge, SPIRE
    User->>Wizard: Click "Create"
    end

    rect rgb(254, 226, 226)
    Note over Backend,KC: Authentication
    Backend->>Backend: Validate namespace against allow-list
    Backend->>KC: client_credentials grant (kagenti-api client)
    KC-->>Backend: JWT with SPIFFE audience scopes
    end

    rect rgb(209, 250, 229)
    Note over Backend,K8s: Agent Creation
    Backend->>RHAO: POST /api/v1/agents (Bearer token)
    RHAO->>K8s: Create Deployment
    RHAO->>K8s: Create Service
    RHAO->>K8s: Create Route/HTTPRoute
    RHAO-->>Backend: {success: true, name, namespace}
    end

    rect rgb(219, 234, 254)
    Note over Backend: Governance Registration
    Backend->>Backend: chatAgents.push({agentId, stage: draft, createdBy: userRef})
    Backend-->>Wizard: KagentiCreateAgentResponse
    end

    Wizard->>UI: Close wizard, switch to My Agents tab
    K8s->>Pod: Schedule pod + pull container image
    Pod->>Pod: Start agent server on port 8000

    rect rgb(243, 232, 255)
    Note over UI,Pod: Test Chat
    User->>UI: Click agent > Test tab
    UI->>Backend: POST /chat/stream (model=ns/name)
    Backend->>RHAO: POST /api/v1/chat/ns/name/stream
    RHAO->>Pod: Forward A2A request
    Pod-->>RHAO: SSE stream events
    RHAO-->>Backend: Forward stream
    Backend-->>UI: stream.text.delta events
    UI->>UI: Display agent response
    end
